<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-1199 </DOCNO><TEXT>Although the rate of new orders for nuclear power plants is down dramaticallyand fewer plants are under construction, the number connected to thegrid has steadily increased. This has prompted a shift of emphasis innuclear safety from the design and construction of plants to their operation.At the same time, there is growing recognition that mere compliance withregulatory requirements is not enough, that excellence in operationalsafety must be achieved for the public to support renewed expansion ofnuclear power. For its part, the IAEA is continuing to develop programmesthat can help its Member States and operating organizations achieve thisgoal. Four of these - known by the acronyms OSART, OSIP, ASSET and IRS- are the subject of this article.</TEXT></DOC>